HEADWORD: bomb calorimeter
<hw>bomb" cal`o*rim"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a type
of calorimeter made of a steel body which closes tightly and resists
high pressure, designed for measuring the amount of heat developed
during chemical combustion of a quantity of combustible material in an
oxygen atmosphere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

